Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.98,0:00:45.14,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(287.795,679.091)\fade(255,0,255,0,380,3820,4140)}Cáo Cāo \NStyled: Mèngdé
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.27,0:00:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Liu Bei has left Xǔdū,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.68,0:00:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,just as Fengxiao had said!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.08,0:00:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,By releasing the enemy one day, I have brought everlasting trouble upon myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.72,0:00:59.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.74,0:01:02.58,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(232.46,666.818)\fade(255,0,255,0,740,2000,2860)}Xún Yù\NStyled: Wénruò
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.96,0:01:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Che Zhou is a trusted subordinate.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.56,0:01:12.06,Default,,0,0,0,,He was originally intended to be govern over Xú-Province.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.37,0:01:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You can send a letter to Che Zhou and order him to think of a way to kill Liu Bei.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.49,0:01:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Chen Deng has come.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.02,0:01:41.74,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(806.032,503.182)\fade(255,0,255,0,660,2000,2700)}Chē Zhòu
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.84,0:01:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Lord Che, what have you summoned \Nme for?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.11,0:02:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The Chancellor has sent me a secret letter, telling me to get rid of Liu Bei immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.35,0:02:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,This way, he can avoid future trouble. \NI have called you to discuss this matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.59,0:02:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.66,0:02:12.38,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(279.661,666.818)\fade(255,0,255,0,380,2350,2700)}Chén Dēng \N Styled: Yuánlóng
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.99,0:02:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Liu Bei has received an order to suppress \NYuan Shu, thus gaining merits from the court.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.00,0:02:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Why does the Chancellor want to kill him?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.47,0:02:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, he has won the hearts of Xú-Province's citizens.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.31,0:02:28.22,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,I know the people burnt incense and blocked the streets
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.28,0:02:31.65,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,just to ask the Chancellor to have Liu Bei manage Xú-Province.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.85,0:02:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,That hasn't changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.02,0:02:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,However, when the Chancellor gives an order, how can we refuse?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.83,0:02:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Liu Bei will eventually return after pacifying the people.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.04,0:02:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You can set up an ambush \Noutside the city and engage him.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.74,0:03:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I will hold off his rearguard using crossbows from the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.58,0:03:06.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.08,0:03:11.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We shall follow your plan, Yuanlong.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.15,0:03:14.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I take my leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.06,0:03:20.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Yuanlong.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.96,0:03:25.34,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,If we can work together with one heart and mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.92,0:03:28.73,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,we can report the success to the Chancellor.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.84,0:03:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.15,0:03:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,General Chen, what irks for you to come here?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.00,0:03:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Che Zhou was ordered by the Chancellor to kill Liu Bei!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.66,0:03:45.18,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1227.935,646.364)}Guān Yǔ\NStyled: Yúncháng
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.85,0:03:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Che Zhou has placed 1,000 troops outside the city
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.85,0:03:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,to attack the imperial uncle when he returns!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.78,0:03:50.58,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1209.586,644.318)\fade(255,0,255,0,340,1500,1780)}Zhāng Fēi\NStyled: Yìdé
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.86,0:03:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That bastard Che Zhou! I will kill his entire force!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.28,0:03:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Che Zhou is already prepared. \NIf we act rashly, we will be defeated.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.97,0:04:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Better to think of a plan to capture him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.60,0:04:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Plans, plans, plans! Let's see if that bastard\N Che Zhou can stop my serpent spear!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.48,0:04:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother, you must restrain yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.84,0:04:10.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.83,0:04:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's goes?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.04,0:04:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,General Zhang Liao, sent by Chancellor Cao!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.61,0:04:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait until I report to general Che.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.64,0:04:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Report it quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.18,0:04:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,General Che.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.18,0:04:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Yuanlong, what is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.95,0:04:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Why didn't you open the gates for them?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.76,0:04:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,If they're the Chancellor's troops, he will be suspicious if I don't let them in,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.36,0:05:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,but if they're not and I go \Nwelcome them, I fear it's a trap.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.63,0:05:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yuanlong, I can't be at ease since \NI placed my men into an ambush.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.50,0:05:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I think this issue does not bode well.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.18,0:05:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you the army of General Zhang?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.26,0:05:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.72,0:05:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's hard to identify people at night. \NStation your troops outside for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.95,0:05:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,After dawn, you may enter the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.06,0:05:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But Liu Bei is onto us! \NWe can't wait, open the gates now!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.97,0:05:40.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Yuanlong, look there!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.94,0:05:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yuanlong?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.31,0:05:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yuanlong!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.08,0:05:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yuanlong!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.48,0:05:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Have the ambush troops follow me\N outside the city to investigate.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.30,0:05:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.77,0:06:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is General Zhang?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.55,0:06:26.42,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,Wretch, You dare plot to kill my brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.42,0:06:27.33,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,Prepare to die!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.35,0:06:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Open the gate! Open the gate!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.95,0:06:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I have showed the Chancellor's letter to General Guan.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.19,0:06:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,If you changed your mind, please \Nget off your horse and surrender, general!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.38,0:06:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Chen Deng, you traitor!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.74,0:06:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You have led me into your trap, but I will kill you!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.08,0:06:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,General Guan!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.31,0:06:55.13,Default,,0,0,0,,General Guan, your blade is too hasty!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.32,0:07:11.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Second Brother and Yuanlong,\N thank you for welcoming me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.14,0:07:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is Third Brother and Inspector Che?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.90,0:07:27.06,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(180,636.136)\fade(255,0,255,0,500,2500,3140)}Liú Bèi\NStyled: Xuándé
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.14,0:07:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to tell you myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.84,0:07:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,That traitor, Che Zhou, tried to kill you, so I took his head.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.75,0:07:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Would he really try to do such a thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.59,0:07:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn't Che Zhou's idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.06,0:07:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The one who wanted to kill the Imperial Uncle was Cao Cao!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.93,0:07:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's Yide?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.50,0:07:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,He wanted to kill Che Zhou's family in vengeance, he's in the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.41,0:08:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Is he trying to ruin me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.71,0:08:32.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Elder Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.00,0:08:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Elder Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.54,0:08:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I have exterminated Che Zhou's entire...!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.96,0:08:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Elder Brother, the one who deserved it is dead,\N but those who didn't are dead too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.00,0:08:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the use of lamenting anymore?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.17,0:09:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Who should we kill? Who shouldn't we kill?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.88,0:09:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Che Zhou was a trusted officer of Cao Cao. Didn't you know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.42,0:09:20.72,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,{\blur11.25}When we left Xuchang,\N you said it yourself, brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.72,0:09:23.09,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,From now on, we would no longer be tied back.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.26,0:09:27.29,Default,,0,0,0,,If we must kill, then kill we shall! Isn't it too late to regret it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.66,0:09:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Too late?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.13,0:09:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,If Cao Cao has an excuse to raise \Ntroops against us, what are we going to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.84,0:09:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry, brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.31,0:09:43.87,Default,,0,0,0,,When Cao Cao comes, Yide and I will meet him and that will be it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.99,0:09:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Second and Third Brothers, you are mistaken.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.46,0:10:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Your unworthy brother knows that you don't fear Cao Cao,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.80,0:10:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,but we have just come back to \NXú-Province without a secure foothold.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.80,0:10:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, our men are few and provisions scarce. What do we have to boast about?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.98,0:10:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,If the people of Xu-Province get caught up in war once more...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.58,0:10:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,because of us...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.39,0:10:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Elder Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.59,0:10:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Lord Xuande, you needn't worry. I have a plan that can fend off Cao Cao.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.73,0:10:43.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now, the only one Cao Cao fears is Yuan Shao.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.24,0:10:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yuan Shao watches over Ji, Qing, You, and Bing provinces.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.36,0:10:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,His army numbers a million; he has a myriad of talents.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.75,0:10:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not send a message to Yuan Shao asking for reinforcements?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.32,0:11:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I have never made contact with Yuan Shao.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.72,0:11:04.40,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,I had just defeated his younger brother, Yuan Shu.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.27,0:11:07.04,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,Why would he want to help me?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.44,0:11:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a man who has had good relations with the Yuan family for three generations.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.04,0:11:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,If he writes a letter, Yuan Shao will certainly send help.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.14,0:11:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Lord Xuande, why not try?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.24,0:11:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Elder Brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.38,0:11:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Liu Bei just destroyed my brother, \Nso I did not want to help him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.39,0:11:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,However, he had {\i1}Master Zheng Xuan{\i0} send a letter, asking for help.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.62,0:11:36.26,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1205.468,662.727)\fade(255,0,255,0,520,2120,2620)}Yuán Shào\NStyled: Běnchū
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.53,0:11:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Master Zheng...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.38,0:11:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Master Zheng...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.89,0:11:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Liu Xuande is a hero of our age.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.58,0:12:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,If I listen to Master Zheng and aid Liu to oppose Cao,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.02,0:12:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,what would you all think?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.90,0:12:07.90,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.16,0:12:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}After years of raising troops, \Nthe people have suffered greatly.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.29,0:12:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}The granaries are empty and taxes are heavier by the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.80,0:12:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}We cannot draft more into your grand army!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.62,0:12:21.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}We could claim victories to the Son of Heaven.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.32,0:12:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}If we can't reach the Emperor,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.10,0:12:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}then we can memorialize that\N Cao Cao has been abusing power.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.36,0:12:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)} After that, we only need to station troops at Liyang.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.08,0:12:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}Concurrently, we can use our righteous army to launch an expedition against the rebel,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.06,0:12:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}and settle the land within 3 years!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.39,0:12:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Tian Feng is right!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.66,0:12:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.14,0:12:46.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}His words are improper.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.44,0:12:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}With your divine might and the strength of the north,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.76,0:12:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}destroying Cao Cao is as easy as turning one's palm.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.72,0:12:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}What need is there\N for a three-year plan?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.98,0:13:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}If we hold off, it may ruin your great plans.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.86,0:13:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}Your words make sense!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.79,0:13:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}Wanting to pacify such a scourge\N will make the army feel righteous.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.40,0:13:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}Yet confident from their numbers, the army is arrogant.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.40,0:13:17.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}A righteous army is strong,\N but an arrogant army will perish.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.80,0:13:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}Cao Cao's laws are pragmatic and his men are well trained.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.42,0:13:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}If we don't use the 'petition' strategy
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.42,0:13:24.38,Note (Potential style?),,0,0,0,,Tian Feng's strategy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.24,0:13:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}and instead raise nameless troops,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.24,0:13:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}then our army will be at a disadvantage.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.60,0:13:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}I beseech for you to reconsider.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.24,0:13:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.84,0:13:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}He is wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.20,0:13:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}Our men are better than Cao Cao's. \NHow could they be called 'nameless'?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.72,0:13:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}Our warriors are brave; our men are in high spirits.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.82,0:13:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}If we don't settle this matter swiftly, we will be inviting disaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.06,0:13:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}I ask that you listen to Master Zheng, my lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.46,0:13:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}Join Liu Bei in his righteousness and destroy that rebel, Cao Cao.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.90,0:13:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}This is the wish of both Heaven and the people.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.10,0:14:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Gentlemen!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.77,0:14:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,All of your words seem reasonable,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.65,0:14:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,but it is hard to discern who is right and who is wrong. What should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.29,0:14:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Master Zheng...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.70,0:15:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor, if your migraine is unbearable, why don't you rest for a while?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.55,0:15:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,If Liu Bei makes contact with Yuan Shao and ally together, what can I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.36,0:15:35.16,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,We can't underestimate Yuan Shao's power.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.99,0:15:39.62,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,We can't send men at the moment. We can only ask for peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.43,0:15:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Yuan Shao is a incompetent fellow. What need is there for peace?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.70,0:15:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}Sir, you are mistaken.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.52,0:15:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}Yuan Shao's territories are vast and strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.02,0:15:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}His subordinates, such as {\i1}Xǔ Yōu,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.20,0:15:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)\i1}Guō Tú, Shěn Pèi, Páng Ji,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.48,0:16:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}are all wise strategists.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.00,0:16:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}There is also {\i1}Tián Fēng{\i0} and \N{\i1}Jǔ Shòu{\i0}. Both are loyal ministers.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.30,0:16:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)\i1}Yan Liang{\i0} and {\i1}Wen Chou{\i0} are men of peerless bravery.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.36,0:16:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}Others, like {\i1}Gāo Lǎn, Zhāng Hé, {\i0}and{\i1} Chúnyú Qióng,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.56,0:16:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}are all renowned generals of the land.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.56,0:16:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}Sir, why say that Yuan Shao is a incompetent fellow?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.44,0:16:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}Even though Yuan Shao's troops and warriors are numerous,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.40,0:16:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}his laws aren't scrupulous and his discipline lacking.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.17,0:16:45.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}Tian Feng is willful but obstinate; \NXu You is gluttonous but not bright;
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.24,0:16:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}Shen Pei is devoted but not resourceful; and Pang Ji is resolute but inept.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.60,0:16:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}All these people are incompatible with each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.88,0:17:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}Sooner or later, there will be internal conflict.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.62,0:17:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}Furthermore, Yuan Shao relies on the numbers and is indecisive.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.00,0:17:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}Even with thousands of his men, how can he succeed?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.50,0:17:24.88,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(462.273,535.909)}Jǔ Shòu
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.95,0:17:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Report!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.36,0:17:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Report, my lord! Master Xu You is here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.80,0:17:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Gentlemen.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.37,0:17:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Gentlemen!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.58,0:18:09.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Lord Xu has a lot of insight. \NLet's listen to what he has to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.86,0:18:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.93,0:18:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Lord Xu, you came at the right time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.10,0:18:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Master Zheng has asked me to send reinforcements to Liu Bei against Cao Cao.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.54,0:18:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Should I mobilize the army or not? Please enlighten me, Lord Xu.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.82,0:18:42.54,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(220.222,644.318)\fade(255,0,255,0,620,2000,2700)}Xǔ Yōu\NStyled: Zǐyuǎn
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.83,0:18:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}My lord, if you use the many to invade the few \Nand use the strong to attack the weak,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.08,0:18:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}you can punish the rebels and restore the ruling house.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.34,0:19:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}You must mobilize an army!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.54,0:19:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}Lord Xu, that is exactly what I thought of!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.90,0:19:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}I want Shen Pei and Pang Ji to oversee conscription.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.58,0:19:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}Tian Feng and Xu You will be my advisors.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.20,0:19:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}Yan Liang and Wen Chou will be my commanders.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.70,0:19:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}Gather 150,000 cavalry and 150,000 infantry,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.16,0:19:27.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}a total of 300,000!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.43,0:19:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}Have them march to Liyang at once!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.67,0:19:32.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.14,0:19:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.07,0:19:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord, if we are to justly punish \NCao Cao, we must first list his vices.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.31,0:19:44.55,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,Send a declaration of war to every commandery, denouncing him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.55,0:19:47.48,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,This is the proper way of doing things.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.25,0:19:48.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Excellent!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.35,0:19:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Kongzhang?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.56,0:19:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.03,0:20:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Enumerate the many crimes of Cao Cao and send it to every commandery.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.37,0:20:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.42,0:20:06.70,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(220.199,685.227)\fade(255,0,255,0,620,1660,2260)}Chén Lín\NStyled: Kǒngzhāng
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.38,0:20:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}Of old, the strength of Qin was debased by a weak ruler, thus Zhao Gao domineered.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.80,0:20:15.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}Empire acted to his bidding, \Nit's wealth and power behest to his whims,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.48,0:20:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}for those against him were subdued, and none dared to speak with candor.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.11,0:20:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}To this end there came to be the Disaster of Wangyi, the massacre of many families.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.11,0:20:26.72,Note (Potential style?),,0,0,0,,Note: Referring to late Qin dynasty, when Zhao Gao forced Qin Er Shi to commit suicide in order to gain more power.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.76,0:20:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}Reviled to this day,\N forever is his name served as a warning.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.99,0:20:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did you stop reading?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.27,0:20:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep reading.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.77,0:20:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't stop without my orders.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.08,0:20:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)\i1}The Ducal Minister of Works, Cáo Cāo,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.16,0:20:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}whose grandfather was the Regular Attendant Cao Teng, who, with Zuo Guan
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.98,0:21:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}and Xú Huáng, tormentors of the common men, \Nviolate the state with depravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.16,0:21:03.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}His father, Cao Song, this eunuch-adopted groveler,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.66,0:21:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}with his venal false-name, now a briber of the powerful,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.40,0:21:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}stealer of titles, and corrupter of imperium.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.80,0:21:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}Cao Cao, his obscenity inherent,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.75,0:21:19.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}loves only to carnage, revels only in ruin...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.00,0:21:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,,My... my head feels better now!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.99,0:22:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Who wrote this Essay of Denunciation?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.20,0:22:20.10,Note (Potential style?),,0,0,0,,Essays of Denunciation (檄文) were manifestos written as condemnations of character and declaration of war, written as far back as the Xia-Shang dynasties and as late as 1920s.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.39,0:22:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I have heard it comes from Chen Lin's own hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.57,0:22:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who write these letters need to back it up with real spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.91,0:22:31.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though Chen Lin's style is excellent, it's a shame...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.08,0:22:35.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that Yuan Shao's strategy is lacking!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.75,0:22:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,His strategy is lacking!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.19,0:22:43.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor, Yuan Shao and his 350,000 army are marching from Liyang.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.93,0:22:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Call everybody here to discuss. We must prepare!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.86,0:22:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.78,0:23:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Liu Dai and Wang Zhong!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.89,0:23:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Here!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.58,0:23:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You two will lead 50,000 men.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.25,0:23:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The vanguard will be Liu Dai \Nand the rear will be Wang Zhong!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.38,0:23:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,When you march out, you will go to Xú-Province and attack Liu Bei!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.82,0:23:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.80,0:23:25.69,Default,,0,0,0,,After Generals Liu and Wang have set out,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.49,0:23:30.59,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,the rest are to follow me towards Liyang to counter Yuan Shao.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.17,0:23:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Understood!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.04,0:23:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Bring us the commander's banner.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.55,0:23:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Give it to general's Liu and Wang.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.90,0:23:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.30,0:23:42.90,Default,,0,0,0,,This...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.36,0:23:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,This is your own banner.\N How could we dare to fly it in your name?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.31,0:24:15.65,Default,,0,0,0,,An order for you to fly my own banner when attacking Xú-Province
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.05,0:24:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,is just to make an empty show of strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.69,0:24:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you've set up camp, don't advance recklessly.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.59,0:24:28.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Once I have defeated Yuan Shao, I will march to defeat Liu Bei.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.87,0:24:40.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.00,0:24:41.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.45,0:24:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Excellent.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.82,0:25:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if the Chancellor has already arrived at Liyang.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.10,0:25:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm more concerned about when he can go to Xú-Province.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.58,0:25:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The Chancellor's army should come as fast as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.60,0:25:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,That way, I can return this banner, lest it be destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.54,0:25:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no need to worry about someone as irrelevant as Liu Bei.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.21,0:25:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,When we arrive to Xu-Province, just send someone to Hebei
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.16,0:25:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,to inform the Chancellor, nothing more.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.12,0:25:29.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Elder Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.96,0:25:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Our spies at Hebei have returned!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.30,0:25:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,How is the military situation?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.17,0:25:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Yuan and Cao have not \Nengaged in combat yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.00,0:25:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,They haven't engaged yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.26,0:25:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.47,0:25:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Have some water and explain!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.35,0:25:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yuan and Cao have brought their men. Even though their armies are fierce,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.18,0:25:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Liyang has a strong defense. They're locked in a stalemate.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.00,0:26:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Why won't they fight?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.80,0:26:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}It's said Xu You is unhappy with Shen Pei's command.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.52,0:26:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}Ju Shou resents that Yuan Shao hasn't used his advice.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.64,0:26:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}All have selfish motives and won't press the attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.36,0:26:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}Yuan Shao was unable to make up his mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.64,0:26:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}Now that he is even more uncertain, he will not make a move.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.30,0:26:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}And why won't Cao Cao make a move?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.84,0:26:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}I couldn't get enough information.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.72,0:26:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}I only heard that Cao Cao ordered Lü Bu's former general, Zang Ba, to guard Qing- and Xu-provinces.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.28,0:26:32.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}Yu Jin and Li Dian are along the Yellow River. \NCao Cao himself has stationed his men at Guandu.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.66,0:26:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is Cao Cao now?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.26,0:26:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,He could be at Liyang. \NHe could be at Xǔdū (Xǔchāng). He could be at...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.33,0:26:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Where?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.77,0:26:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,At Xú-Province!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.46,0:26:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.44,0:26:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,If he's in Xú-Province,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.28,0:27:05.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Then if this is true, then doesn't that mean \NCao Cao is the one camped outside?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.78,0:27:23.94,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(184.091,697.5)\fade(255,0,255,0,380,2820,3140)}Wáng Zhōng
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.19,0:27:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The Chancellor didn't engage Yuan Shao. He's come back to Xǔdū secretly.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.46,0:27:53.43,Default,,0,0,0,,When he left, he ordered us to meet Liu Bei in battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.66,0:27:57.94,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(379.972,672.955)\fade(255,0,255,0,380,3860,4260)}Liú Dài \NStyled: Gōngshān
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.47,0:27:57.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Why won't you attack, General?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.91,0:28:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Liu Bei is a clever man.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.95,0:28:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,If he discovers the Chancellor is not in the camp
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.15,0:28:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,he will join up with Yuan Shao.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.58,0:28:15.34,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,How can you sit idly and not seize this opportunity?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.34,0:28:18.40,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,How would you explain it before the Chancellor?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.79,0:28:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Since the Chancellor has ordered us to attack, you go first.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.93,0:28:27.93,Default,,0,0,0,,He has ordered you to go first.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.77,0:28:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I am the commanding general.\NHow could I go?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.47,0:28:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's stop arguing over who is the commander.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.27,0:28:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Per the orders of the Chancellor, we'll attack together.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.71,0:28:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.81,0:28:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it proper to fight over who goes first?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.49,0:28:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's draw lots. Whoever draws the written note goes first.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.43,0:28:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine, let's draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.97,0:29:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to write them again!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.74,0:29:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't back down now, General. \NMarch at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.41,0:29:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.15,0:29:49.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The Cao army have left camp to march here.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.96,0:29:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Whose banner do they have?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.34,0:29:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The center holds Cao's.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.99,0:29:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't wait for their armies to attack us!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.56,0:30:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Elder Brother, send me with Second Brother to meet the enemy!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.42,0:30:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}I heard Cao Cao's banner is nowhere to be seen in Liyang.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.19,0:30:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}Why is his banner here, instead?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.50,0:30:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}Cao Cao is full of tricks\N and likes to supervise battles himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.02,0:30:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}Thus, he decided not to fly his banner at Liyang,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.60,0:30:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,877.5)}which means the banner is being falsely raised here. \NI think Cao Cao is actually not here!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.32,0:30:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We can send somebody to find out the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.25,0:30:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to go!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.72,0:30:28.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You're too reckless and violent.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.89,0:30:33.20,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,If the commander in the center really is Cao Cao,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.24,0:30:35.42,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,I will capture him and bring him to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.16,0:30:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Elder Brother, I can scout out.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.20,0:30:46.77,Default,,0,0,0,,If you go, Yunchang, I can be at peace. You may bring 3,000 men with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.57,0:30:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Third Brother, defend the city. I'll be right back.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.51,0:30:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You only need to find out whether that's really Cao Cao!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.67,0:31:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Elder Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.10,0:31:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Elder Brother, you may ask this man about the truth!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.01,0:31:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And who may you be?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.35,0:31:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is Wang Zhong.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.25,0:31:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,What rank do you hold?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.59,0:31:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I am an assistant officer under Chancellor Cao.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.32,0:31:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Preposterous! How dare you march \Nunder the Chancellor's banner?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.19,0:31:43.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't dare! I was only following orders!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.76,0:31:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,He ordered me to use his reputation to confuse the troops.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.24,0:31:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is Cao Cao now?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.14,0:31:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,That...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.70,0:31:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Speak!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.15,0:32:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,He's already returned to Xǔdū!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.36,0:32:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Men.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.30,0:32:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Here!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.93,0:32:16.13,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,Prepare clothes and food for General Wang and put him in jail.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.93,0:32:19.60,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,We'll discuss what to do once we have Liu Dai.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.07,0:32:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.05,0:32:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all thanks to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.49,0:32:41.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Elder Brother,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.26,0:32:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I shouldn't have killed Che Zhou, so I brought Wang Zhong alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.90,0:32:52.60,Default,,0,0,0,,This way you may use him in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.13,0:33:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You were only keeping me safe. What are you saying? If anything, I should be ashamed!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.11,0:33:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Elder Brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.80,0:33:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Second Brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.94,0:33:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Elder Brother! Now that Wang Zhong is captured, let me go for Liu Dai!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.63,0:33:25.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Liu Dai was the Overseer of Shandong. When we fought Dong Zhuo at Hulao Gate,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.97,0:33:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,he too was one of the lords there. \NWe can't underestimate him.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.01,0:33:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,What can someone like him do?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.97,0:33:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, like Second Brother, I will just bring him here alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.14,0:33:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I just fear that you will take his life and ruin my cause.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.68,0:33:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,If I kill him, you may take my head!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.59,0:33:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.16,0:33:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I will give you another 3,000 men. Bring Liu Dai to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.60,0:34:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Liu Dai, you coward! Come out if you can!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.52,0:34:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Insult them! As much as you can!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.49,0:34:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Insult him! Louder!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.09,0:34:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, insult them!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.29,0:34:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Insult them until dusk. See if they can stand it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.43,0:34:34.61,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,I cannot accept that my brother can take Wang Zhong alive,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.61,0:34:37.00,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,but I can only throw empty insults!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.87,0:34:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Get up! Keep insulting them! Now!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.88,0:34:45.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Curse them!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.18,0:34:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Curse them! Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.40,0:34:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Liu Dai, you coward!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.66,0:34:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you curse his ancestors?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.24,0:34:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We did!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.89,0:34:59.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Liu Dai must be furious!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.10,0:35:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,He hasn't even stirred!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.96,0:35:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,General Zhang!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.03,0:35:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Beat him up!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.00,0:35:42.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Harder!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.98,0:35:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,General Zhang, a few strikes is enough. Must you be so angry?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.62,0:36:03.05,Default,,0,0,0,,That's my own business as a general! It has nothing to do with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.56,0:36:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Pass down my orders.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.93,0:36:11.25,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,That rat Liu Dai doesn't even leave his camp!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.95,0:36:15.57,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,He just stays in his camp, doing who knows what!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.04,0:36:19.77,Default,,0,0,0,,If he doesn't come, I'll go to him!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.87,0:36:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,General?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.78,0:36:26.82,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,Tell every camp to ready the troops.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.39,0:36:31.38,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,Tonight, at the third watch, we shall lead a surprise attack on their camp.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.78,0:36:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll break down their gates!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.15,0:36:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you capture the camp if you are drunk?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.89,0:36:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Can we not postpone?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.09,0:36:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Coward!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.03,0:36:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just a few liters of wine.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.97,0:36:49.79,Default,,0,0,0,,How can that intoxicate me?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.20,0:36:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Pass down my orders. Everyone must prepare.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.88,0:36:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.21,0:36:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And also...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.45,0:37:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,don't forget to tie this soldier real tight.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.48,0:37:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,When we strike the enemy... I'll... I'll offer him as a sacrifice before the banner!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.16,0:37:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.05,0:37:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,That Zhang Fei said...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.45,0:37:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,that he would offer me as a sacrifice \Nbefore attacking the camp!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.54,0:38:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So that Zhang Fei is just a reckless idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.94,0:38:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a few days without fighting and that's enough to work him up.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.15,0:38:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the opportunity for us to meet one plan with another.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.12,0:38:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Let him bring his troops to an empty camp.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.99,0:38:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll lure him into my trap!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.36,0:38:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I reckon that soldier is at Liu Dai's camp.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.84,0:39:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We will go by three separate ways at the third watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.07,0:39:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll lead the elite troops and cut off his rear.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.88,0:39:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,On the middle route, thirty men will sneak into their camp and light a fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.55,0:39:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The two other groups will launch a surprise attack against Liu Dai when they see the fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.79,0:39:26.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.16,0:39:32.02,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,I wagered my own head before my brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.70,0:39:36.37,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,If someone kills Liu Dai, I will kill the offender!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.57,0:39:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Officers, do you understand me?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.66,0:39:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Understood!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.24,0:39:46.58,Default,,0,0,0,,That's good. Don't you forget it!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.78,0:39:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Understood!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.98,0:39:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Pass my orders! It's the third watch! We will assault their camp!
